Oh yeah. :)

It was quite an awful movie, but I just had to tell the group about a 
few scenes of interest.

Quick synopsis:
Jason Vorhees, invincible homicidal maniac, is cryogenically frozen in 
2000-something and thawed out again on a space station in 
2400-something.  He starts killing people again and eventually 
encounters a bunch of nano-bots that give him an upgrade.

It's particularly interesting to see how (comparatively) low-budget, 
b-rated flicks like this portray the freezing/unfreezing and 
nano-medicine processes.  There wasn't anything quite like a "utility 
fog", but it did a better job of portraying limb-reconstruction than 
the Fifth Element (in which an entire body was replaced).  Oh, also 
worth mentioning, there were a few scenes involving 25th century video 
games - which as you might guess have a strong holo-deck/VR feel to 
them.

Anyway, if you have a strong stomach and/or a penchant for morbid 
humor, head on down to your locally-owned rental outlet and pick this 
one up.

