To all cryonicists:

The Creekside Preserve is planning an open house on Sunday, October 26th to show off our new facility.   All cryonicists are invited to a tour and complimentary buffet luncheon on Sunday afternoon.

We are hoping that in the future the Creekside Preserve will become a place of frequent cryonics and life extension meetings, conferences, celebrations, weddings, memorial services and more.  It is also our hope that the Creekside Preserve and its amenities will become part of a larger cryonics community someday, one that will include a retirement village and other opportunities for cryonics and life extension advancements.

For those of you that might want to come up Saturday evening, we will be having a fireside get-together at the firepit by the creek and a walk to our observatory.  Rooms or cabins for cryonicists will be 25% off.

                OUR FEATURED SPEAKER ON SUNDAY WILL BE DR. JERRY LEMLER,                                                 ALCOR'S CEO AND DISTINGUISHED LEADER. 

Here is an agenda:
Saturday evening = fireside discussion and social get-together.
Saturday evening = walk up to our observatory and we all look at the heavens above.

Sunday
Morning nature walk for about an hour's exercise.  
Then a tour of the property and a visit to the barn to pet and feed the horses.  
Noon to 1:00 = buffet 
1:00 Dr. Lemler will address the audience.

This is an informal event for all cryonicists of every persuasion, come up for fun and meet other cryonicists.  Perhaps, Dr. Lemler will even give us a preview of what to expect at the coming Alcor Conference in November?

                       ============================================

How to get to the Creekside Preserve, which is about an hour's drive from north Phoenix.

1.    Drive north from Phoenix on Interstate-17 (as if you were going to Flagstaff).
2.    About 40 miles or so, you come to the town of Cordes Junction.  Exit.
3.    Then go west (or northwest) on State Highway 69 (towards Prescott - but not all the way). 4.    Six miles from Cordes Junction is the Creekside Preserve on the north side of the highway.


Our phone number is 928  632-0777  (But we are not manning the phone until around October 12th).  In the meantime, please e-mail me any questions or let me know if you are expecting to come.  

Below is a list of what we have so far.
15 individual cabins that have porches that hang over the creek area.
A 9,000 square foot lodge with 4 rooms upstairs (these rooms are kinda plain).
Some cabins have Jacuzzi tubs
All cabins have fireplaces
A barn where you can bring your horse or you can pet ours
An observatory
Lots of hiking trails
Meeting rooms

The following may be open by then, or soon thereafter:
Exercise room
Conference room = holds 60 to 80 people
Restaurant for our guests
Volleyball court
horseshoe pits

Later
More cabins
Swimming pool
library of life extension
museum of cryonics and life extension
retirement center

Please send me, or post, your thoughts, ideas, suggestions.

