I should have emphasized 'continuation' of subjective experience, which I
guess I skipped over in typing that particular message.  As I have
emphasized from the get go, a copy will not experience the same subjective
events that a reference or original does, thus it CAN NOT be a continuation
of the consciousness of the original.  

Consider, a reference may be copied *without his knowledge* if a copy was
truly a continuation of a particular identity (by my definition) then he
would experience what the copy does.  If he does not, then they are two,
distinct, separate, isolated entities.

