in "identity" since the same atoms are unlikely to be involved in the
different substrates.  Obviously people can handle the "shift" from 10:00 PM
one evening to 7:00 AM the next morning.  They also seem to be able to handle
the shift from being put under general anesthesia until they wake up
and even being in a coma for a number of years (though this is rare).
It raises some interesting issues regarding cryonic suspension as to
whether a person can retain an identity when the down time in their
subjective experience may be 30-100 years or more, particularly in light
of the accelerating changes one might expect from the singularity.

